The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Bengal kick off vs Nagaland today

 Kochi: Bengal open their campaign in the Santosh Trophy on Saturday when they will take on Nagaland. 

The tournaments most successful team ? 29-time champions and 10-time runners-up ? has been clubbed in Cluster VIII with Mizoram and Andhra Pradesh, apart from Nagaland. 

On Monday, Bengal will face Andhra Pradesh and two days later, they will end the preliminary stage with the match against Mizoram. 

Bengal are being coached by Aloke Mukherjee and Biswajit Das. 

Mukherjee, however, sounded confident of emerging the cluster champions, on the eve of their opener. 

Both captain Bhaichung Bhutia and Mehtab Hussain have been stuck up with problems regarding their release back home and are unlikely to feature in the first two matches. But Mukherjee maintained that despite their absence, teams morale is high. 

 (AGENCIES) 




